annotationA: Unpaired 3 (Upd3) is a "cytokine" (secreted protein) of the Unpaired family that can bind and activate the JAK-STAT receptor dome. Upd3 is induced in hemocytes or in the intestine upon damage to regulate the repair response in these tissues through JAK-STAT activation
annotationB: Unpaired 2 (Upd2) is a secreted molecule that acts at a distance as a ligand for the JAK/STAT signal transduction pathway. Upd2 mutants are viable due to redundancy with other Upd-family genes
